{"id":67863,"title":"Glomerulopathy in adult recipients of pediatric kidneys.","abstract":"To compare \"for cause\" renal biopsies (bx) from adult recipients of pediatric-donor kidneys (PDK) versus adult-donor kidneys (ADKs), we reviewed 103 graft bx from 50 PDK recipients and 85 bx from 49 ADK recipients. PDK bx displayed more frequent glomerular pathology with immune complex-mediated glomerulonephritis present in 11/103 PDK versus 1/85 ADK (p < 0.05). In 15/103 PDK bx and 1/85 ADK (p = 0.001), the association of glomerular sclerosis, expanded mesangium, and halo of prominent podocytes by light microscopy, and ultrastructural glomerular basement membrane lamellation, configured a characteristic glomerulopathy.","date":"2014-03-10","categories":"Male Urogenital Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24579775","annotations":[{"name":"Basement membrane","weight":0.835773,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basement_membrane"},{"name":"Glomerulonephritis","weight":0.814942,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glomerulonephritis"},{"name":"Biopsy","weight":0.787886,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biopsy"},{"name":"Light microscopy","weight":0.784822,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Light_microscopy"},{"name":"Kidney","weight":0.749237,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kidney"},{"name":"Glomerulus","weight":0.741322,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glomerulus"},{"name":"Microscopy","weight":0.714354,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microscopy"},{"name":"Mesangium","weight":0.668451,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mesangium"},{"name":"Podocyte","weight":0.621504,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Podocyte"},{"name":"Pathology","weight":0.578186,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathology"},{"name":"Cell membrane","weight":0.239407,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_